LAYOUT (TEXT="Generic Menu Test")
GRID
{
Style   [d01                                             ]
Comment [d02                                             ]
Image   [d03                                             ]
<T                                                       >
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
 [c01       |c02         |c03       |c04                ]
<                                                        >
[bg01                                                    ]

 In this example, you can build up a menu generically i.e. maybe from a 
 database or set of configuration files. Type into the array some additional
 menu entries and click the button. The only restriction is the maximum
 number of entries, in this instance 20. I haven't got them here but you
 could add other methods to change the accelerator attribtue.
}
END
END

ATTRIBUTES

COMBOBOX d01 = formonly.STYLE, ITEMS=(("dialog","Dialog"),("popup","Popup"));
EDIT d02 = formonly.COMMENT;
EDIT d03 = formonly.IMAGE;

c01 = formonly.name, SCROLL, COMMENT = "Enter the action name", TITLE="Name";
c02 = formonly.text, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu text", TITLE="Text";
c03 = formonly.item_image, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu image", TITLE="Image";
c04 = formonly.item_comment, SCROLL, COMMENT="Enter the menu comment", TITLE="Comment";
BUTTON bg01: menu, TEXT="Show Menu", COMMENT="Show menu";

INSTRUCTIONS
SCREEN RECORD scr(name,text,item_image,item_comment);
